Basically it means you're going to charm one mob and let a bunch of his friends beat him nearly to death and then kill him yourself. Repeat with his friends until all are dead.<br>
<br>
How do we do it?<br>
* Make sure you have a &quot;/pet attack&quot; hotkey.<br>
* Mem,<br>
   - Fufil's Curtaling Chant<br>
   - Tuyen's Chant of Flame<br>
   - Tuyen's Chant of Frost<br>
   - Solon's Song of the Sirens or Solon's Bewitching Bravura (depending on your level and the level of the mobs)<br>
   - Hymn of Restoration or Cantata of Replenishment<br>
   - Selo's Accelerando or Selo's Accelerating Chorus<br>
   - rest are optional<br>
* Equip yuor best drum.<br>
* Start Selo's (I shouldn't be telling you this, it should be up by default <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). Preferably the L49 version. For those that haven't heard about it, that's the 2.5 minute version of the regular Selo's.<br>
* Find a pack of social mobs. By 'social' I mean that they will help a friend if they see him fighting someone else.<br>
* Charm one of them, if resisted re-try until he's under your control.<br>
* Hit your &quot;Target nearest enemy&quot; key. (Default is F8 I think, I got mine remapped to &quot;Q&quot;)<br>
* Hit your &quot;/pet attack&quot; hotkey.<br>
* Quickly hit F1 twice. (First F1 will target you, second your pet)<br>
* When charm breaks, and you think your former pet will survive another round, repeat.<br>
* If your former pet is low on life, chant kite it to death.<br>
* Charm one of the your now dead pets friends and repeat until they're all dead.<br>
<br>
So, what the hell does all that mean?<br>
When you charm your first pet, he will be running for you and start pacing back and forth like all obedient pets do.<br>
When he is close enough to hear the &quot;/pet attack&quot; command he will go after your target. His buddies will all start wailing on your pet, since they don't like stuff hitting their friends.<br>
What you have now is 3 mobs hitting on your pet, who will most likely loose if they keep this up. But as a bard, you're in luck here. Charm only lasts about 15 seconds. After that they will all come after you. If you're lucky your pet will be really low on health and you can kill it off for XP, if not recharm it.<br>
If your pet should aggro more than 3 mobs, the rest will come after you. Don't worry, just run around with them on your tail until charm breaks.<br>
<br>
A few things to remember:<br>
* Remember to refresh Selo's when it drops.<br>
* You have to be close to your pet for him to hear your &quot;/pet attack&quot; command. You will most likely get hit a couple of times getting the hang of this. Just start Hymn or Cantata when the mobs are fighting each other. If you have singing steel BP, just click it (90 HP heal).<br>
* If your pet gets the kill on a mob while he's still under your spell, you will only get half XP.<br>
* If your pet should get killed, the corpse will poof and you get no XP.<br>
<br>
As an optional, if you have a singing steel bracer, you can buff your pet with a damage shield. That way all the mobs hitting on him will take even more damage.<br>
